subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution and habitat. The new species was found in areas of the Cerrado Biome in Minas Gerais state and Distrito Federal ( Fig. 11 ), respectively in the southeastern and central-western regions from Brazil , Good’s biogeographic zone 27 of the Neotropical Region ( Good 1974 ). Following the Köppen-Geiger system, the type locality ( Minas Gerais state ) has a Subtropical Highland Temperate climate (Cwb), characterized by a dry winter and warm summer, and an annual average temperature below 22 °C. In the Distrito Federal region, the climate is of a tropical savanna (Aw/As), with an annual average temperature above 18 °C and precipitation less than 100 mm (
Kottek et al. 2006
).
